<subSubSection id="C368650B321D9807FF4817E2FD0AFE51" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BCD3680321D9806FF4817E2FD22F80C" blockId="22.[151,1436,1765,2006]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="B906EA92321D9806FF4817E2FEF5F927" bold="true" box="[151,329,1765,1790]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Type material.</emphasis>
Describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03321D9806FE0517E1FCAAF927" authority="Suffrian (1866)" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[474,790,1765,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilotus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92321D9806FE0517E1FDE6F924" box="[474,602,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. spilotus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B71321D9806FDBA17E2FCAAF927" author="Suffrian, E." box="[613,790,1765,1790]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 483" refId="ref45438" refString="Suffrian, E. (1866) Zur Kenntniss der Sudamerikanischen Cryptocephalen. Linnaea Entomologica, 16, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1866">Suffrian (1866)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
wrote: “ 
<collectingCountry id="F3657610321D9806FCA117E2FC59F927" box="[894,997,1765,1790]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
(Mus. Schaum) ... in einem einzigen stücke ... 
<specimenCount id="9D74FD09321D9806FEDD160DFEABF8F8" box="[258,279,1802,1825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
unbekannt”. Therefore, the female housed in 
<collectionCode id="ED63AE45321D9806FCC3160DFC38F8F8" box="[796,900,1802,1825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">MNHUB</collectionCode>
and labelled: “America, collect. Schaum” must be considered the 
<typeStatus id="54C98822321D9806FEBB162AFE7AF89F" box="[356,454,1837,1862]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species. Anyway, there is not a complete correspondence between the label data and what Suffrian registered in his monography (see also what has been said on the subject in relation to 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03321D9806FAA21655FEB8F854" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corruptus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92321D9806FAA21655FEB8F854" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. corruptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In my opinion this shows that in identifying the types of the species described by Suffrian, it is necessary to interpret wisely the information available, without persisting too much in the search of a complete correspondence between the different sources.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD3680321C9807FF181190FDB4FEC5" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="23" pageNumber="80">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C98822321C9807FEDC1190FED9FF69" box="[259,357,151,176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="80">holotype</typeStatus>
is identified as follows. 
<typeStatus id="54C98822321C9807FD78119BFCA1FF76" box="[679,797,156,175]" pageId="23" pageNumber="80">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
